<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="199" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,288,1359]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,397,423]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 14.5–16.6; head length: 1.4–1.6; head width: 3.0–3.1; pronotal length: 2.5–3.1; pronotal width: 8.9–9.5; scutellum length: 6.7–7.5; scutellum width: 5.0–5.5; abdominal width: 8.0–8.3; length of antennal segments. I: 0.8–1.0; II: 1.4–1.6; III: 1.0–1.3; IV: 3.5–4.1; V: 4.2–4.5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="199" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,288,1359]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,504,530]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum without black stripe. Anterolateral margin not punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with light brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1144,540,567]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[327,431,576,603]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with narrow brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[930,1032,576,603]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1351,576,603]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore remarkably excavated laterally (
<figureCitation box="[583,706,612,639]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7C–D</figureCitation>
), leaving the parameres visible in lateral view. Dorsal rim rugose and projected posteriorly, surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[908,999,648,675]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup triangular, short, tapering to the base, and close to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1194,684,711]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere spatulate; anterior lobe developed and rounded; posterior lobe well-developed and subtriangular; outer margin black; stalk with inner medial carina low, evanescent and curved toward anterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[994,1117,756,783]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of setae clearly separated by medial bridge; posterior face pentagonal with both lateral margins swollen and somewhat ventrally projected (
<figureCitation box="[498,621,828,855]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7B–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim remarkably projected caudally; medial excavation shallow; expansions slightly tumid, acuminated, and narrow; apices densely setose, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[335,425,900,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[647,734,900,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
). Plates with long and sparse setae. Valvifers 8 subtrapezoidal, posterior margin sinuous; inner angles reaching basal third of valvifers 9, not touching each other; inner margins forming a long and narrow drop-like excavation. Valvulae 9 exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="199" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,288,1359]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1008,1034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Comments.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[390,533,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[390,533,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[586,739,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omegoides">
<emphasis box="[586,739,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. omegoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (
<figureCitation box="[759,893,1008,1035]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 10C–D</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[952,1081,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis box="[952,1081,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[1094,1292,1008,1035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" pagination="401 - 441" refId="ref18209" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. rest. (Heteroptera Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 401 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[1173,1228,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1301,1385,1008,1035]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) has the lateroventral side of the pygophore remarkably excavated, leaving paramere completely exposed laterally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7C–D</figureCitation>
). This condition also gives the impression that ventral rim of the pygophore is strikingly projected caudally, completely different from all other species of the genus. The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[908,1051,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[908,1051,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1103,1256,1116,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omegoides">
<emphasis box="[1103,1256,1116,1142]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. omegoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show the lateral margins of the posterior face of the proctiger ventrally projected (
<figureCitation box="[892,991,1152,1179]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Figs. 7B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1004,1051,1153,1179]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">10B</figureCitation>
) (just surpassing the margin in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and strongly developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[572,727,1188,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omegoides">
<emphasis box="[572,727,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. omegoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Females from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[916,1061,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[916,1061,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[1118,1250,1188,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis box="[1118,1250,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1224,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunes, B. M. &amp; Campos, L. D. &amp; Mendonca, M. T. S. &amp; Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[254,448,1224,1251]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" pagination="401 - 441" refId="ref18209" refString="Nunes, B. M., Campos, L. D., Mendonca, M. T. S., Cunha, E. V. P. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2020) Revision of Hypoxys Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 stat. rest. (Heteroptera Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4742 (3), 401 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Nunes 
<emphasis box="[331,385,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[459,545,1224,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1558,1582]" captionTargetBox="[163,1407,195,1519]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1534]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys bitumidus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). The main difference between these species is the median excavation of valvifers 
<quantity box="[151,193,1260,1287]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[200,341,1261,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis box="[200,341,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[356,438,1260,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[248,1339,193,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-20@13.[228,1359,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Hypoxys excavatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
) that is narrower with apices of inner angles closer to each other than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[1231,1359,1260,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerneri">
<emphasis box="[1231,1359,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">H. boerneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1181,1296,1323]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,288,1359]" box="[199,1181,1296,1323]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1297,1323]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the strongly excavated lateral surface of the pygophore.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
